<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-02-0931 </DOCNO><TEXT>Acoustic waveform analysis has been used to provide a quantitative analysisof the effectiveness of cement grouting for sealing three adjacent boreholesdrilled at Harwell, Oxon, as part of a research programme into the disposalof radioactive wastes into argillaceous formations. Results indicatethat bonding at cement/casing and cement/formation interfaces would beinadequate for sealing a radioactive waste repository and the use ofa backfilling material such as bentonite is advocated. (U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>